latestPosts.caption:
We decided to try Nutty Hot Chocolate Affogato! Turns out, it’s too delicious and way more fun to make than we thought. 😍 Here’s how it went ⬇️ 

🍨 Step 1 -  First, we will make a nice dense hazelnut hot chocolate using 3 tbsp mix in 150ml milk, stirred for 3-4 mins. 

🍨 Step 2 -  Time to grab the fanciest cup we could find. Then we added a big scoop of hazelnut ice cream. No hazelnut? No problem - any good ice cream works. 🙌 

🍨 Step 3 - The fun part! We carved a little hollow in the middle of the ice cream (basically a mini hot chocolate jacuzzi). 😄 Then, we slowly poured the hot chocolate into the hollow and let it flow over the edges. Watching that pour? SO satisfying. 

And that’s it! The dessert was ready. It tasted like warm hugs and cool breezes in one bite. If you try this, tag us - because we know we’re not the only ones who’ll end up eating it straight from the cup! 😅

#hotchocolate #hotbeverage #chocolatedrink #cocoa

I personally don’t like super thick, pudding-like like hot chocolate - it’s just too much for me. So, I usually hunt for cafes that serve lighter, more drinkable hot chocolate. But this time? Big letdown. 😅

If you’re on the same team as me, here’s a recipe to fix your hot chocolate cravings at home:

☕️ 1. In a bowl, add water and milk in a 40:60 ratio. Let it boil. Then add 2-3 tbsp of chocolate mix from @thetiggle_ 

☕️ 2. Heat it on low flame until it boils. You can also add 1-2 cardamoms (ilaichi) for taste. After 3-4 boils, strain it and enjoy it in a ceramic cup or glass. 

Okay, bye! ☁️✨
